    • Method Detail

      • url

        java.net.URL url(long botId)
          throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Used to generate an URL for this endpoint using the specified bot id.

        If requiresBotId() returns TRUE and botId is -1 (See url()), this method will throw an IllegalArgumentException.

        Parameters:
        botId - The ID to insert into the URL.
        Returns:
        The URL.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If no valid ID was provided when an ID was required.

      • requiresBotId

        boolean requiresBotId()
        Checks whether this endpoint requires a bot id to be constructed.
        Returns:
        Whether a bot id is required.

      • url

        default java.net.URL url()
                  throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Used to generate an URL without a bot id parameter.

        If requiresBotId() returns TRUE, this method will throw an IllegalArgumentException.

        Returns:
        The URL.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If requiresBotId() returned TRUE.
